CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 10, 1962, pg. 23A, reads: "Record Stars - The singing Davenport Sisters of Monongahela, Pa., recently had a record released by the Tri-Phi Recording Co. of Detroit. Left to right: Norma, Toni, Sylvia and Florence. The tune, 'You've Got Me Crying Again,' was written by Florence, who also plays the guitar accompaniment. The girls have appeared extensively in night clubs, private parties and banquets. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: The Davenport Sisters band, including Norma, Toni, Sylvia, and Florence with Silvertone guitar, posed in YMCA with banner inscribed "Young Men's Christian Association, Developing Christian Character, Christian Communities"
